WEST NILE VIRUS UPDATE 2003 - CANADA (14)
*****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Sat 16 Aug 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Health Canada, West Nile Virus Surveillance, Wed 13 Aug 2003 [edited]
<http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/pphb-dgspsp/wnv-vwn/mon_e.html>

West Nile virus surveillance data as of Wed 13 Aug 2003
-------------------------------------------------------
Human
-----
Three confirmed cases: One confirmed case in Saskatchewan, a blood donor;
one confirmed case in Alberta , also a blood donor; one confirmed case and
one suspected case in Ontario (possibly contracted in the USA).
Equines
-------
Fifteen confirmed equine cases; Ontario (1), Manitoba (2), Saskatchewan
(7), Alberta (5).
Mosquitoes
----------
As of 7 Aug 2003, 18 pools of mosquitoes have tested positive; Quebec (3),
Ontario (3), Manitoba (2), Alberta (10).
Wild Birds
----------
Test Results by Province:
Province / No. submitted for testing /No. tested / No. confirmed positive
Newfoundland and Labrador / 67 / 62 / 0
Prince Edward Island / 229 / 214 / 0
Nova Scotia / 586 / 607 / 0
New Brunswick / 642 / 559 / 3
Quebec / 1364 / 1273 / 54
