ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The totals for Canada for 2003 so far are 8869 birds submitted for
testing, 8171 birds tested, and 367 confirmed West Nile virus-positive. In
addition there were 2471 sightings of dead birds recorded. This represents
an increase of 576 birds tested and 84 more birds confirmed positive since
the last update on Wed 6 Aug 2003. There have been no extensions of range.
Eight more equine cases have been confirmed, and the number of positive
mosquito pools has increased by 12. A West Nile virus-positive blood
donation has been reported in both Alberta and Saskatchewan, and a
confirmed human case and suspected imported human case in Ontario. - Mod.CP]
